Kiamanga MCA Robert Kibe Githongo is set to appear before the Milimani Anti-Corruption court on Wednesday. The Kiambu county MCA was arrested by EACC officials for allegedly presenting them with forged academic certificates. Githongo will be charged with four counts including provision of false information, making a false document, uttering a false document and making a false declaration. The Anti-corruption commission opened investigations into allegations that the suspect had forged academic certificates to enroll at Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology. Githongo allegedly forged his KCSE certificate in order to be  enrolled  for a diploma in a leadership programme in JKUAT.